02:12.032 --> 02:14.935
That's the word from German
environment Minister Matilda--

02:14.935 --> 02:17.438
- Holy shit, that smells good!

02:22.376 --> 02:23.877
Oh, what happened?

02:23.877 --> 02:25.479
You okay?

02:25.479 --> 02:30.218
- I think it's all right, I
could use a band aid though.

02:30.218 --> 02:33.120
- It looked good, at least.

02:33.120 --> 02:35.889
- I guess we'll just have
to make this salad night.

02:35.889 --> 02:39.427
- You sure, it's not Thursday,
think you can handle it?

02:39.427 --> 02:41.495
- I can improvise.

02:41.495 --> 02:44.732
- Oh chaos, everything
is chaos, I say.

02:45.999 --> 02:49.136
Destruction and flames,
and new torments,

02:49.136 --> 02:52.973
and new tormented
souls I see around me,

02:52.973 --> 02:55.343
wherever I look and
how so ever I turn,

02:55.343 --> 02:56.677
and wherever I gaze.

02:56.677 --> 02:57.511
- Shh.

02:58.512 --> 02:59.747
- What's this?

02:59.747 --> 03:01.782
- Earthquake in Poland,
I guess this nuclear

03:01.782 --> 03:03.584
plant's about to blow.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.253
- Shit, now I feel like an ass.

03:05.253 --> 03:06.720
- As you should.

03:06.720 --> 03:08.155
How was it?

03:08.155 --> 03:09.089
- Huh?

03:09.089 --> 03:09.890
- The lecture, how was it?

03:09.890 --> 03:10.724
- Peruse.

03:11.825 --> 03:13.761
- Very nice, your turn.

03:15.162 --> 03:18.766
- Hmm, it was what it
was, I didn't learn much.

03:20.768 --> 03:22.903
- You don't need
to learn anything,

03:22.903 --> 03:24.972
you know it all all ready.

03:24.972 --> 03:25.806
- Ouch.

03:27.207 --> 03:31.011
- No, oh, shit, that's
not what I mean.

03:31.011 --> 03:32.079
- Uh huh.

03:32.079 --> 03:32.913
- No, really.

03:32.913 --> 03:33.847
- Yup.

03:33.847 --> 03:35.182
- I just mean you're smart.

03:35.182 --> 03:36.317
- Sure.

03:36.317 --> 03:37.150
- That's not what I--

03:37.150 --> 03:38.118
- But that's not what--

03:38.118 --> 03:41.121
- Stop, you know what I meant.

03:41.121 --> 03:42.823
- Tell me again how smart I am.

03:42.823 --> 03:44.057
(laughing)

03:44.057 --> 03:45.259
- While don't you
shut up and grab me

03:45.259 --> 03:47.628
a boiled egg from the
fridge, smart guy.

03:47.628 --> 03:49.563
Do you want an avocado?

03:51.432 --> 03:55.002
- Hey, will you turn
that off for a second.

03:57.538 --> 03:59.006
- What's wrong?

03:59.006 --> 04:02.410
- Nothing, nothing is
wrong, at least I hope not.

04:02.410 --> 04:04.578
All my life, I've looked
at words as though

04:04.578 --> 04:07.180
seeing them for the first time.

04:08.316 --> 04:11.184
I rehearsed this
in my head all day.

04:12.886 --> 04:16.557
Oh, damn it, I had this
all figured out in the car.

04:16.557 --> 04:17.391
Uh, here.

04:28.302 --> 04:32.473
Doubt thou the stars of fire,
doubt that the sun does move,

04:34.608 --> 04:38.779
doubt truth to be a liar,
but never doubt my love.

04:41.181 --> 04:44.184
Calliope Garrard,
will you marry me?

04:50.057 --> 04:52.993
(light soft music)

04:56.864 --> 05:00.968
I know it's not much, I wanted
to get something bigger.

05:05.973 --> 05:08.208
(groaning)

05:15.616 --> 05:18.018
(loud thump)

05:23.857 --> 05:26.460
- [Voiceover] Cali, look at me.

05:38.839 --> 05:41.675
(loud static)

05:41.675 --> 05:42.610
- I'm here.

05:49.683 --> 05:52.953
- Oh, you're awake,
how are we feeling?

05:54.755 --> 05:56.256
- She needs water.

06:03.130 --> 06:05.466
- Looks like we have
had quite a night,

06:05.466 --> 06:07.134
haven't we Calliope?

06:14.442 --> 06:17.945
You wanna tell me
what you remember?

06:17.945 --> 06:20.113
- I just came home.

06:20.113 --> 06:20.948
- Mmm hmm.

06:21.849 --> 06:23.684
- And I cut my finger.

06:26.053 --> 06:26.887
- And?

06:30.891 --> 06:34.962
- Doubt the stars of fire,
did you propose to me?

06:37.297 --> 06:40.200
- So, was it a
stroke or something?

06:41.669 --> 06:43.704
- Well, Calliope experienced
what we call a tonic clonic

06:43.704 --> 06:47.541
event, or what was referred
to as a grand mal seizure

06:47.541 --> 06:49.276
back in the middle ages.

06:49.276 --> 06:50.678
It can be triggered
by a number of things,

06:50.678 --> 06:53.847
stress, malnutrition,
flashing lights,

06:55.516 --> 06:59.520
were you watching television
when this happened?

07:01.522 --> 07:02.422
- Uh, yeah.

07:04.592 --> 07:07.928
- Yeah, okay, tell me,
can you remember having

07:07.928 --> 07:11.098
any strange feelings
the moments preceding?

07:11.098 --> 07:15.002
Dizziness maybe, or a
strong surge of emotions,

07:16.369 --> 07:19.540
altered vision,
hearing, strange smells,

07:19.540 --> 07:23.744
overwhelming sense of deja
vu, anything like that?

07:23.744 --> 07:25.312
- I don't remember.

07:26.880 --> 07:31.051
- Okay, well the seizure
appears to have been idiopathic.

07:32.486 --> 07:33.721
- What does that mean?

07:33.721 --> 07:35.989
- It's a fancy word
for we don't know.

07:35.989 --> 07:39.660
Now, is this the first
time it's happened to you?

07:39.660 --> 07:40.661
- I don't...

07:47.367 --> 07:51.539
I think, when I lived with
Billy, or maybe before.

07:55.543 --> 07:56.476
- Billy?

07:56.476 --> 07:58.712
- And how long ago was that?

08:00.180 --> 08:03.551
- I don't know, maybe
10 years ago, nine.

08:04.618 --> 08:06.019
- Who's Billy?

08:06.019 --> 08:09.022
- [Doctor] Was it
just the one time?

08:11.258 --> 08:12.693
- I was eighteen.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.698
I don't, I don't...

08:19.867 --> 08:23.303
- Okay, well listen,
I want you to relax,

08:25.272 --> 08:27.374
I'm gonna come back in and
check on you in a little bit.

08:27.374 --> 08:30.644
We're gonna keep you overnight
and run some tests, okay?

08:30.644 --> 08:31.712
- Sure, okay.

08:43.756 --> 08:44.925
- Who's Billy?

08:46.393 --> 08:50.898
- [Man] Hey, you wanna know
why they call me dead Billy?

08:50.898 --> 08:53.466
(loud buzzing)

08:56.737 --> 09:00.708
It was '67, '68 maybe,
before the Ted offensive.

09:02.075 --> 09:05.412
They sent us into this
village, north of (mumbles).

09:05.412 --> 09:07.447
Everyone there was
Cong, they said.

09:07.447 --> 09:11.018
There was this black guy,
called him big Charles,

09:11.018 --> 09:14.121
huge motherfucker, but
a sweetheart, you know.

09:14.121 --> 09:18.291
Big Charles sees this
girl, maybe seven or eight,

09:18.291 --> 09:21.028
sitting in a road, out
in front of the huts.

09:21.028 --> 09:25.198
She's crying, he has a candy
bar or something in his pack,

09:26.366 --> 09:27.868
so he goes to her, to
give her the candy,

09:27.868 --> 09:30.904
and she jumps up, throws
something, grenade maybe,

09:30.904 --> 09:33.907
something, and Big Charles
catches it one handed,

09:33.907 --> 09:35.342
and turns his big
dumb eyes to me,

09:35.342 --> 09:37.645
and next thing I
know I'm on my back,

09:37.645 --> 09:39.747
wearing his guts as
a fucking necklace.

09:39.747 --> 09:42.783
I was standing five,
10 feet away maybe,

09:42.783 --> 09:44.317
and I didn't have
a scratch on me.

09:44.317 --> 09:47.387
So everyone says later,
Jesus Christ Billy,

09:47.387 --> 09:51.191
you should have been
fucking dead, right?

09:51.191 --> 09:54.127
And I should have been,
I mean, I know that,

09:54.127 --> 09:56.830
but I didn't even singe
my God damn eyebrows.

09:56.830 --> 10:00.033
So about a month later, we're
in this little bar in Saigon,

10:00.033 --> 10:03.203
and this guy Norman,
big Navajo guy,

10:03.203 --> 10:05.338
he's trying to get me
laid, all those guys,

10:05.338 --> 10:07.975
they thought I was a virgin.

10:07.975 --> 10:11.478
Norm decides he can't
have that in his unit,

10:11.478 --> 10:14.815
so he's talking to
this slope whore,

10:14.815 --> 10:17.651
but she don't speak English,
it's all just GI, GI,

10:17.651 --> 10:20.988
blowie, blowie, fuckie,
fuckie, that sort of thing,

10:20.988 --> 10:24.391
so he's telling her this story
about how I should be dead,

10:24.391 --> 10:27.560
and she lights all up
like a Christmas tree,

10:27.560 --> 10:29.863
because yeah, she
knows that word, dead.

10:29.863 --> 10:33.600
So, she just looks at
me with these big eyes,

10:33.600 --> 10:37.470
and she just shrugs
and says, "Blowie?"

10:37.470 --> 10:39.840
He gives her five bucks, he
takes to me this little room

10:39.840 --> 10:41.608
in the back, and sucks me off.

10:41.608 --> 10:44.544
Took me thirty seconds,
but I swear I damn near

10:44.544 --> 10:48.048
blew a hole in the
back of her skull.

10:48.048 --> 10:51.384
Anyway, I've been
Dead Billy ever since.

10:52.786 --> 10:55.956
(thundering and rain)

11:14.307 --> 11:15.809
(loud knocking)

11:15.809 --> 11:17.544
- Cali, come on, this isn't
funny, just open the door,

11:17.544 --> 11:19.479
I know you're in there.

11:22.182 --> 11:25.685
Cali, I just wanna see
you, open the door!

11:28.388 --> 11:32.225
Come on, I'm gonna stay
here all day, until...

11:34.127 --> 11:35.695
Oh God, what did you
let him do to you.

11:35.695 --> 11:36.997
(door slamming)

11:36.997 --> 11:38.531
- I told you I ran away
from home for a while,

11:38.531 --> 11:40.000
when I was a kid.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.603
- Yeah, but you never
mentioned this Billy.

11:45.739 --> 11:46.673
Who was he?

11:48.976 --> 11:50.878
- Just this guy, a vet.

11:53.280 --> 11:55.115
- [Man] From the Gulf?

11:56.649 --> 11:57.484
- Vietnam.

11:57.484 --> 11:59.486
- Jesus, how old was he?

12:00.720 --> 12:02.622
And you lived with him?

12:05.192 --> 12:07.694
Was it, was it a sexual thing?

12:09.496 --> 12:10.697
- Roy--

12:10.697 --> 12:11.498
- Come on, were you
fucking the guy?

12:11.498 --> 12:13.133
- What do you think?

12:18.371 --> 12:21.809
I don't think I need
to apologize to you.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.980
- [Man 1] Are you okay?

13:27.340 --> 13:30.610
(sorrowful slow music)

16:28.355 --> 16:29.856
(loud squeaking noise)

16:29.856 --> 16:31.958
- [Newscaster] Developing in
Germany, showing a frightening

16:31.958 --> 16:34.527
new discovery at the
Kumps Nuclear Plant,

16:34.527 --> 16:36.596
just days after the
earthquake in Poland

16:36.596 --> 16:39.866
sent the reactor into
complete meltdown.

16:39.866 --> 16:42.769
German officials have now
released data that shows

16:42.769 --> 16:45.672
radiation levels around
Kunps have spiked

16:45.672 --> 16:48.808
to levels much higher than
initial reports suggested.

16:48.808 --> 16:51.911
Reports from both the German
environmental authorities,

16:51.911 --> 16:55.248
and the UN health
organization, show that total

16:55.248 --> 16:58.818
air release of iodine
131 and cecil 137...

16:58.818 --> 17:00.787
- [Man] Hey, look at me.

17:11.731 --> 17:14.401
(alarm beeping)

18:09.156 --> 18:11.824
- Well, this is kinda fucked up.

18:13.226 --> 18:15.695
- There's nothing to
discourage the appetite

18:15.695 --> 18:18.465
