39:40.345 --> 39:44.082
visions narrowing down,
tiny little pinprick.

39:47.152 --> 39:49.588
Want me to countdown for you?

39:50.922 --> 39:53.191
30, 29, 28, 27, 26, enough?

39:58.196 --> 40:00.799
(loud gasping)

40:18.349 --> 40:20.786
That's what it's like to die.

40:40.105 --> 40:42.373
That guy, Starkey's friend,

40:44.209 --> 40:48.379
that dude you were talking to
at the VFW, what was his name?

40:52.784 --> 40:55.353
His name Calliope, what was it?

40:57.222 --> 40:59.224
- I don't, I don't know.

41:08.099 --> 41:09.200
- I think he liked you.

41:09.200 --> 41:11.870
(light sobbing)

41:17.509 --> 41:20.846
You can go out with
him, if you want to.

41:22.614 --> 41:25.116
I mean, if you really want to.

41:46.337 --> 41:48.774
(loud thump)

41:54.245 --> 41:56.915
(phone ringing)

42:01.119 --> 42:02.520
- Hello.

42:02.520 --> 42:03.989
- [Roy] Hey, I was
thinking about stopping by

42:03.989 --> 42:06.892
that new vegan thai place on
my way home, you want anything?

42:06.892 --> 42:08.326
- Yeah, pad thai.

42:09.661 --> 42:12.931
- [Roy] Tofu, egg
noodles, right?

42:12.931 --> 42:14.199
- Yeah.

42:14.199 --> 42:16.568
- [Roy] And a ton of
hot stuff, I got it.

42:16.568 --> 42:17.636
(loud thump)

42:17.636 --> 42:19.738
You want a thai iced tea?

42:21.406 --> 42:22.574
Hey, you okay?

42:24.610 --> 42:28.680
- Um, no, just banged my
elbow on the gear shift.

42:32.083 --> 42:34.319
No iced tea, thanks though.

42:36.421 --> 42:39.157
- [Roy] Okay, you home?

42:39.157 --> 42:41.459
- I'll be home in
a few, I'm just out

42:41.459 --> 42:43.561
running a couple errands.

42:43.561 --> 42:45.997
- [Roy] You doing okay?

42:45.997 --> 42:47.098
- Yeah, yeah, just--

42:47.098 --> 42:49.134
(loud thump)

42:49.134 --> 42:49.968
Um, shit.

42:51.169 --> 42:52.738
- [Roy] You okay?

42:52.738 --> 42:56.341
- No, the batteries crapping
out, I'll see you in a bit.

42:56.341 --> 42:57.843
- [Roy] Mmm, okay.

43:16.662 --> 43:18.897
(knocking)

43:27.973 --> 43:32.143
- There's nothing I can
say to stop you, is there?

43:36.314 --> 43:40.218
And you know that this
is really stupid, right?

43:43.421 --> 43:46.257
I don't know where
he is, after...

43:50.361 --> 43:54.199
You know, he just sort
of dropped off our radar.

43:54.199 --> 43:56.868
You'll have to trust me on that.

43:57.803 --> 43:58.636
- Okay.

44:09.614 --> 44:13.618
- You need to know that
this could get me fired.

44:25.864 --> 44:30.035
Alissa Kononen, she's a stand
up comic out of Brooklyn.

44:31.202 --> 44:34.239
After you left, I
did a quick search.

44:34.239 --> 44:37.743
She's on the road right
now, she's doing clubs

44:37.743 --> 44:39.677
all across the country.

44:41.112 --> 44:43.915
I don't have her number, but
if you're up for a drive,

44:43.915 --> 44:48.386
she's performing down in
the Springs, this Saturday.

44:48.386 --> 44:51.823
Maybe you could catch
her after the show.

44:55.360 --> 44:56.962
She's his daughter.

45:03.434 --> 45:07.105
Calliope, this cannot
come back on me, okay?

45:12.543 --> 45:13.544
- Of course.

45:19.050 --> 45:21.052
- Take care of yourself.

45:29.795 --> 45:32.463
(train horn whistling)

45:32.463 --> 45:34.132
- Yeah, okay, I get.

45:37.168 --> 45:39.004
No, I understand, I...

45:41.306 --> 45:42.640
I do Kay, but...

45:47.245 --> 45:50.515
Can't you just put
her on the pho...

45:50.515 --> 45:54.619
All right, well at least
tell her happy birthday.

46:25.783 --> 46:26.617
- Morning.

46:32.858 --> 46:34.860
- [Cali] Is it epilepsy?

46:36.327 --> 46:39.697
- Epilepsy's a fairly useless
term, but no I don't think so.

46:39.697 --> 46:40.598
Looky here.

46:42.033 --> 46:45.136
Not a tumor, don't worry, it
appears to be a small lesion,

46:45.136 --> 46:47.973
about the size of
your pinky nail.

46:49.374 --> 46:53.211
And it appears to have
been there for some time.

46:54.712 --> 46:58.183
Tell me, Calliope, have
you been seeing things,

46:58.183 --> 47:01.519
or hearing voices, or
anything like that?

47:04.089 --> 47:06.057
You know, there's no
percentage in not being

47:06.057 --> 47:08.393
honest about this, Calliope.

47:12.197 --> 47:15.133
Okay, well first
thing, no more TV.

47:16.434 --> 47:19.337
Not until we get
this taken care of.

47:19.337 --> 47:21.239
- What are the options?

47:22.908 --> 47:27.078
- Well, considering the
seizures and hallucinations,

47:28.446 --> 47:30.548
and whatnot, I'd say
we're pretty well past the

47:30.548 --> 47:32.150
wait and see stage.

47:32.150 --> 47:34.986
Now, I doubt this is
cancer, but we'll need to do

47:34.986 --> 47:37.722
a biopsy to rule it out.

47:37.722 --> 47:39.991
In the meantime, no
TV, try not to drive,

47:39.991 --> 47:43.061
blah, blah, blah,
you know the drill.

47:51.702 --> 47:54.705
Don't worry, this is nothing.

47:54.705 --> 47:57.642
It's a little pit
stop, that's all.

47:58.876 --> 48:01.146
Congratulations, by the way.

48:18.163 --> 48:19.430
- It's okay Billy.

48:19.430 --> 48:21.799
- What the fuck do
you know about it?

48:21.799 --> 48:24.035
Shit, fuck, I'm sorry Cali.

48:26.237 --> 48:27.172
I love you.

48:31.042 --> 48:33.278
(gurgling)

49:00.238 --> 49:03.374
- We have rotted wood all
underneath the sink here.

49:03.374 --> 49:04.642
- I found this.

49:08.113 --> 49:10.715
Under the bed, Billy drew this?

49:15.453 --> 49:16.287
- No.

49:21.926 --> 49:23.861
That was somebody else.

49:25.630 --> 49:29.034
- Calliope, you
need to talk to me.

49:29.034 --> 49:30.568
- Roy, not right now.

49:30.568 --> 49:33.071
- No, I've had enough of this.

49:34.639 --> 49:37.575
Do you understand
what this is like?

49:37.575 --> 49:39.777
Do you get it, at all?

49:39.777 --> 49:42.080
I'm trying so hard, Cali,

49:42.080 --> 49:44.315
to not think you're
just a fucking liar,

49:44.315 --> 49:47.085
and everything you've
told me about yourself is

49:47.085 --> 49:49.954
a fucking lie, and the life
we've been building together,

49:49.954 --> 49:50.955
is a fucking lie.

49:50.955 --> 49:51.889
- Roy--

49:51.889 --> 49:53.991
- Are you a fucking liar, Cali?

49:53.991 --> 49:54.925
Talk to me!

49:54.925 --> 49:56.927
- Roy, you're hurting me!

50:01.399 --> 50:03.468
- Calliope, fuck, I am...

50:07.838 --> 50:11.276
- It's your birthday
next month, 18, wow.

50:12.843 --> 50:15.913
We should do something,
have a party.

50:17.915 --> 50:20.251
Oh wait I forgot,
that will never work,

50:20.251 --> 50:22.487
you don't have any friends.

50:24.522 --> 50:26.023
- Mom.

50:26.023 --> 50:28.626
- You know, in a month,
you're gonna be an adult,

50:28.626 --> 50:30.328
and then you can do
whatever the hell you want,

50:30.328 --> 50:32.563
but while you're
here, in my house--

50:32.563 --> 50:33.764
- Mom.

50:33.764 --> 50:34.432
- [Mother] You
will do exactly...

50:34.432 --> 50:35.800
- Just stop it.

50:35.800 --> 50:36.634
- What?

50:38.103 --> 50:41.672
- Just stop with the whole
concerned parent thing.

50:41.672 --> 50:43.841
You don't do it very well.

50:48.913 --> 50:51.282
- You're really something else,

50:51.282 --> 50:52.583
after everything I have done--

50:52.583 --> 50:54.985
(loud thump)

50:56.521 --> 50:59.390
You wanna go back to him?

50:59.390 --> 51:00.558
- Dad?

51:00.558 --> 51:03.128
- You know who I
mean, where were you?

51:03.128 --> 51:04.229
- I told you.

51:06.631 --> 51:10.201
- Yeah, your dads,
should I call him?

51:10.201 --> 51:13.104
(low solemn music)

51:17.242 --> 51:18.075
- Oh, I don't think I'm
supposed to have any of that.

51:18.075 --> 51:19.510
- I made it weak.

51:35.260 --> 51:37.262
So, tell me about Billy.

51:53.311 --> 51:55.546
- She was gorgeous, I mean,

51:57.148 --> 52:00.385
not movie gorgeous
or anything, just...

52:02.753 --> 52:04.489
First thing I thought
when I saw her,

52:04.489 --> 52:07.892
was how tired she was,
that nobody that young

52:07.892 --> 52:09.960
should be so God damn tired.

52:09.960 --> 52:12.963
She had these deep sunk
eyes, that just dug in

52:12.963 --> 52:16.634
like corkscrews, and
this thin little mouth,

52:18.469 --> 52:22.407
that I thought, I don't
know, I kind of thought,

52:22.407 --> 52:24.242
I just wanted to kiss.

52:25.810 --> 52:28.179
I always wanna fuck the
girls when I see them.

52:28.179 --> 52:30.181
I can't seem to help it.

52:31.682 --> 52:35.019
My eyes are words
straight to my prick,

52:35.019 --> 52:37.555
doesn't matter who they are.

52:37.555 --> 52:39.156
The first thing I think
when I see them is

52:39.156 --> 52:44.161
how I wanna get them naked,
I wanna get them under me.

52:44.161 --> 52:47.598
And I wanna fuck the God
damn shit out of them.

52:47.598 --> 52:50.100
But with her, all I wanted is,

52:52.470 --> 52:55.740
I just kind of wanted that kiss.

52:55.740 --> 52:58.175
All I thought about for days.

52:59.377 --> 53:02.880
I should've left
it there, I guess.

53:02.880 --> 53:05.783
I thought she could
make me normal,

53:06.951 --> 53:08.619
I've never been with
a normal girl before,

53:08.619 --> 53:12.390
but I thought, I don't
know, maybe she could do it.

53:12.390 --> 53:14.892
Maybe I could love her normal.

53:16.427 --> 53:19.464
And then when she was gone,

53:19.464 --> 53:24.001
I felt like my chest
was this big black cave.

53:24.001 --> 53:28.205
I was 17 God damn years old,
and I felt like it was over.

53:28.205 --> 53:29.139
I was dead.

53:32.042 --> 53:35.079
I guess maybe that's why
they call me Dead Billy.

53:35.079 --> 53:37.415
I know what you're thinking,

53:38.816 --> 53:42.653
I know what you wanna
do, don't think I don't.

53:46.891 --> 53:49.260
It's okay, you know.

53:49.260 --> 53:50.595
Hey, look at me.

54:01.171 --> 54:02.006
It's okay.

54:17.688 --> 54:18.889
(quiet sizzling)

54:18.889 --> 54:21.626
It's okay Cali, it's
okay, it's okay.

54:28.366 --> 54:30.134
It's okay, it's okay.

54:39.009 --> 54:41.178
- [Roy] How long were you?

54:42.913 --> 54:44.515
- I don't remember.

54:56.093 --> 54:59.664
- Come on, I'm not
paying by the hour here.

55:07.137 --> 55:10.541
- A long time, I think
they took me away.

55:12.710 --> 55:14.311
- Who?

55:14.311 --> 55:16.481
- A social worker, my mom.

55:21.218 --> 55:24.389
I think I was 17
when they got me out.

55:25.823 --> 55:29.059
- You know it wasn't
your fault, right?

55:31.929 --> 55:34.432
Calliope, you were just a kid.

55:37.001 --> 55:38.769
It wasn't your fault.

55:40.871 --> 55:44.041
(low sorrowful music)

55:53.083 --> 55:54.619
- You're lovely.

55:54.619 --> 55:55.786
- Calliope.

55:55.786 --> 55:57.121
- Roy, listen...

56:01.726 --> 56:02.827
Listen to me.

56:07.965 --> 56:09.700
I wanted to be there.

56:14.872 --> 56:17.775
